(File, Nielen de Klerk, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - An illegal miner was killed and another wounded in a shoot-out with the police in Benoni, east of Johannesburg, on Thursday.Police spokesperson Major Mack Mngomezulu said Ekurhuleni Metro Police and SAPS officers came under fire when they responded to a report of a shooting between illegal miners in the area."One illegal miner died on the scene and another was rushed to hospital under police guard," said Mngomezulu in a statement.Two people were arrested, 14 rounds for an R5 rifle were seized and several explosive devices were found at the scene.The area has been a hotspot of unrest involving illegal miners, with five bodies found in the area last Saturday.Last month, two girls were injured after being hit by stray bullets while playing on a mine dump in the area during an apparent shooting involving illegal miners. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.